adjectives.description: unfavorite (comparative more unfavorite, superlative most unfavorite)

entries.meaning: (informal) Not preferred; in particular, especially disliked.
(informal) Something that is not a favourite; particularly something that is especially disliked.

verbs.description: unfavorite (third-person singular simple present unfavorites, present participle unfavoriting, simple past and past participle unfavorited)

entries.meaning: (Internet, transitive) To remove from one’s list of favorites.
examples: How do I unfavorite a tweet?
